post.body: Time to use this site once and never visit it again, just like I do with regular Twitter

Got my CD-i 220 this afternoon, booted it up, found out the disc motor wouldn't spin, spent a couple hours figuring out how to loosen it up, then realized the Timekeeper had died and I now need to either replace the chip or scrape it down, remove the embedded battery and solder in a new battery holder.

Philips can go to hell with this one.

CD-i update: Timekeeper battery replaced after hours of digging into the chip and dodgy soldering, VCDs seem to work but I still can't boot games up because I'm obviously not burning them right.

Alright, let's figure this one out.
Turns out I was just burning dodgy disc images. The CD-i is online.

Keto/low carb is great until that great weight loss plateau hits

Been stuck at the same weight for like the past 2-3 months so I've just decided to say fuck it and carb it up for the rest of the month
guess i'll start muting the chinaposters since i can't understand their moonrunes

I honestly expected to see more CP posted here considering I've seen a few self-confessed pedos pop up

That is not an invitation

This 8 months or so of doing security work have been a real eye opener for me. Mainly because they've made me hate retail security and developed my rather negative opinion on the defense forces, whom I was just about to be put out to work with. 

Fuck man, why can't I just open a small little store and sell retro gaming stuff at reasonable prices? I don't want to be doing this security shit anymore unless I can get the real cushy static jobs my mate from the course is getting. Sick of busting my ass in retail doing 4 hour shifts for the same pay as he does for doing nothing.
Current mood: 10:30 Maccas run on a Sunday night with my cock out
Real shame that all the cool people aren't on Zerome anymore. Now it's just the Chinese.

thinking about buying an rv and just being a drifter moving about the country broadcasting pirate radio stations 

what are the government going to do? tell me to move on?
